Sojourn

The inert atmosphere thrives,
  sends forth the wind
      in crimson,
    and acts like heaven;
      how quickly the flood can,
  associating truth,  and
  the supple reasoning 
      of blooming petals—
  imperceptible language,
  yet nature will mention dusk.


- Marianne Moore
